article.headline: UC Irvine 76, San Jose State 55
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- Ross Schraeder scored 26 points, including a career-high eight 3-pointers, in helping UC Irvine gain a 76-55 victory over San Jose State on Friday night. Friday was UC Irvine's second straight road game win. The Anteaters (4-2) had lost 11 straight away from home before beating Santa Clara on Tuesday. UC Irvine has won three straight overall. Jeff Gloger added 11 points. Marquin Chandler scored 24 points for the Spartans (3-5), who lost their third straight. Matt Misko recorded his first career double-double with 10 points and 11 rebounds. Schraeder was 8-of-13 from long range, and made his only two-point attempt. It was the 41st meeting between the two schools, but the first since San Jose State left the Big West Conference after the 1996 season. UC Irvine never trailed in the second half after building a double-digit advantage. The Spartans were within six at 50-44 but the Anteaters went on a 14-2 run to take an 18-point edge into the final four minutes. The Anteaters took an early 10-point lead thanks to some long-range sharpshooting from Schraeder and Nic Campbell but San Jose State rallied to tie at 26. Schraeder sank consecutive 3-pointers to help give UC Irvine a 34-28 halftime advantage.
